ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='I see that `common.js` has empty step definitions for all the auth st
eps. The `.js` files in `step-definitions/` auto-bind these steps. The `auth_log
in.steps.ts` file is separate and not used by the Jest config (which only matche
s `.steps.js`). But the review specifically mentions the `.ts` file.\n\nHowever,
looking at the jest config for BDD:\n```js\ntestMatch: [\'<rootDir>/tests/bdd/st
ep-definitions/*.steps.js\'],\n```\n\nSo only `.steps.js` files are run. The `au
th_login.steps.ts` is not part of the BDD test execution. But the review mention
s it as an issue. I should probably:\n1. Update `auth_login.steps.ts` to have re
al implementations\n2. Also update `common.js` to have real implementations for 
the auth steps\n3. OR maybe the `.ts` file should be converted to `.js` or the j
est config should include `.ts` files.\n\nWait, the review says "BDD Step Defini
tions 全为 `// TODO` 占位符；旧单元测试文件未被清理导致测试套件失败". The `.ts` 
file has `// TODO` comments. The `common.js` file doesn\'t have TODO comments bu
t has empty functions. \n\nFor the BDD tests to actually work, I need to impleme
nt the step definitions in `common.js` because that\'s what\'s actually being ex
ecuted. The `auth_login.steps.ts` might be a red herring or an old file.\n\nActu
ally, looking at the file list again:\n- `tests/bdd/step-definitions/auth_login.
steps.ts` - TypeScript file with TODOs\n- `tests/bdd/step-definitions/auth_login
_phone_number_login.steps.js` - JS file that uses `common.js`\n- etc.\n\nThe `.t
s` file is not used by jest. But the review specifically mentions it. Let me che
ck if maybe the jest config was supposed to include `.ts` files. The BDD jest co
nfig says `moduleFileExtensions: [\'js\', \'json\']` and `testMatch: [\'<rootDir
>/tests/bdd/step-definitions/*.steps.js\']`. \n\nI think the best approach is:\n
1. Implement the actual step definitions in `common.js` (since that\'s what runs
)\n2. Delete or update `auth_login.steps.ts` to match, or maybe convert it to a 
`.steps.ts` that gets compiled. But the jest config doesn\'t include `.ts`.\n\nA
ctually, looking at the PR body, it says "BDD Step Definitions 骨架" which sugge
sts they knew it was just skeleton. The review asks to implement them.\n\nGiven 
the time constraints and complexity, let me focus on:\n1. Backend P0 fixes (old 
test, any filter, last_login_at, OpenAPI update, type regen)\n2. Mobile fixes (D
I, typed models, hardcoded URL)\n3. BDD step definitions in `common.js`\n4. SMS 
rate limiting in AuthService\n\nLet me start making changes. I\'ll work on multi
ple files in parallel where possible.\n\nFirst, let me do the backend changes:\n
