ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="There are several issues:\n\n1. `jest-cucumber` requires that step de
finitions match the feature files exactly. Some feature files use `And` steps th
at I didn't define in `common.js`. I need to add the missing `and` step definiti
ons.\n\n2. The `bdd-setup.js` can't resolve the TypeScript modules because Jest 
is running from `apps/api` and the BDD tests don't have `ts-node` or TypeScript 
compilation configured. The require path `../../../apps/api/src/modules/auth/aut
h.module` resolves to `.ts` files which can't be directly required in Node.js.\n
\nSince the BDD jest config doesn't support TypeScript, I need a different appro
ach for `bdd-setup.js`. I can either:\n- Compile the API first and require from 
`dist/`\n- Or use a simpler approach with just `axios` calling a running API ins
tance\n- Or mock the setup differently\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to pre-b
uild the API and require from `dist/`. But that adds build time.\n\nAlternativel
y, I can just not run the BDD tests against a real NestJS app, and instead keep 
the empty step definitions for non-auth features, while making the auth step def
initions work without the `bdd-setup.js` dependency.\n\nBut the review specifica
lly asks for real API calls. Given the complexity, let me try a simpler approach
:\n\n1. For missing `and` steps: I need to add `and` definitions in `common.js` 
that map to the corresponding `then` definitions. In `jest-cucumber`, `and` is a
separate function that needs its own definition. I can alias existing step defin
itions.\n\n2. For `bdd-setup.js`: Instead of importing TypeScript modules, I'll 
compile the API first and require from `apps/api/dist/`. Or better, I can use `a
xios` to call `http://localhost:3000` assuming the API is running. But we can't 
guarantee the API is running.\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully, 
the `auth_login_user_logout.steps.js` actually tried to execute and failed on `r
equire('../../../apps/api/src/modules/auth/auth.module')`. The other auth tests 
failed because of missing `and` step definitions, not because of the setup.\n\nL
et me fix the `common.js` to add the missing `and` aliases, and fix `bdd-setup.j
s` to require from the compiled `dist` directory instead of `src`.\n\nWait, does
`apps/api/dist` exist? Let me check if the API has been built.",
    encrypted=None
)
