ep-binding.js`:\n\n```js\nvar globalSteps = [];\n```\n\nThis is a MODULE-LEVEL v
ariable in `jest-cucumber`. When Jest runs multiple test files in parallel or se
quence, they all share the SAME `jest-cucumber` module instance (because Jest ca
ches node_modules). So `globalSteps` accumulates step definitions from ALL previ
ously loaded step definition files.\n\nWhen `common.js` is loaded by the first B
DD test file (e.g., `infrastructure_bootstrap...steps.js`), ALL steps from `comm
on.js` are added to `globalSteps`. Then when the auth test file runs, `auth-comm
on.js` adds its steps to `globalSteps` as well.\n\nNow, for the auth registratio
n scenario, `jest-cucumber` iterates over the scenario steps and tries to find m
atches in `globalSteps`. The problem is that `globalSteps` now contains BOTH `co
mmon.js` steps AND `auth-common.js` steps. For some auth steps, there might be M
ULTIPLE matches!\n\nFor example, `And the response code should be 0` might match
