r in the placeholders:\n```js\nthen(\'the response code should be {int}\', () =>
{});  // empty placeholder?\n```\n\nNo, I don\'t think I have an empty placehold
er for that specific step. But I DO have many empty placeholders for similar aut
h steps.\n\nActually, looking at `common.js`, I removed the auth step definition
s from it and put them in `auth-common.js`. But `common.js` still has empty plac
eholders like:\n```js\nthen(\'the user should receive an access token\', () => {
});\nthen(\'the user should land on the home screen if profile is complete\', ()
=> {});\n```\n\nThese don\'t match `the user should receive an access_token and 
a refresh_token` exactly, but `jest-cucumber`\'s `matchSteps` does exact string 
matching for string patterns (case-insensitive). So no collision there.\n\nBut w
ait - if `globalSteps` accumulates across test files, then by the time the auth 
