    think='I see the problem! The steps are duplicated in `common.js` - lines 51
8 and 520 have duplicates of `when(\'the user sends a swipe request via API\')` 
and `then(\'the message should prompt completing profile first\')`. And the `the
n(\'the "reports" table...\')` exists at line 428 but might also have duplicates
.\n\nBut more importantly, there are DUPLICATES in `common.js`! This means `glob
alSteps` gets multiple identical entries, causing `matches.length > 1` for those
steps, which means `options.defineStep` is NOT called, reducing the step definit
ion count.\n\nAlso, I notice that `then(\'the "reports" table should exist...\')
` is defined at line 428, but `autoBindSteps` says only 2 step definitions are f
ound for `infrastructure_bootstrap_security_and_compliance_baseline`. The featur
e has 3 steps:\n1. `Given the database migrations have been applied` - found\n2.
`Then the "blocks" table should exist...` - found\n3. `And the "reports" table s
hould exist...` - NOT found (because of duplicate matches or some other issue)\n
\nWait, I also have the `authThenAlias` in `common.js` which duplicates many ste
ps. And there are empty placeholder definitions for the same patterns.\n\n`commo
n.js` has become a complete mess with duplicates. The `autoBindSteps` mechanism 
with `globalSteps` is fundamentally broken when the same module is loaded multip
le times or has duplicate definitions.\n\nI think the cleanest fix is to remove 
ALL the auth step definitions from `common.js` (since auth now uses dedicated `.
steps.js` files with `defineFeature`), and also remove the duplicates. Then only
the non-auth placeholder steps remain in `common.js`.\n\nActually, looking back 
at my edits, I added auth steps to `common.js` before creating `auth-common.js`,
and then I also added `authThenAlias` duplicates. The auth steps should all be r
emoved from `common.js` now.\n\nLet me just rewrite `common.js` to contain only 
the non-auth placeholder steps, with NO duplicates. This will fix the `autoBindS
teps` issues for non-auth tests.',
    encrypted=None
)
