ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="Now I understand the issue completely!\n\n`createAutoBindSteps` uses 
a `globalSteps` array that is NEVER CLEARED between calls to `autoBindSteps`. It
's a module-level variable:\n\n```js\nvar globalSteps = [];\nvar registerStep = 
function (stepMatcher, stepFunction) {\n    globalSteps.push({ stepMatcher: step
Matcher, stepFunction: stepFunction });\n};\n```\n\nWhen `autoBindSteps` is call
ed for the first feature file (e.g., `infrastructure_bootstrap_security_and_comp
liance_baseline.steps.js`), it loads `common.js` which registers ALL its steps i
nto `globalSteps`. Then when the next auth `.steps.js` file calls `autoBindSteps
(feature, [authCommonSteps])`, it adds the auth steps to `globalSteps` as well.\
n\nBut here's the problem: `globalSteps` is shared across ALL test files. So whe
n the auth test runs, `globalSteps` contains steps from BOTH `common.js` and `au
th-common.js`. This should actually HELP, not hurt.\n\nWait, but `common.js` is 
NOT imported by the auth `.steps.js` files anymore - I changed them to only impo
rt `auth-common.js`. So `globalSteps` should only contain auth steps for the aut
h tests.\n\nBut why does `jest-cucumber` say only 1 step definition is defined? 
Let me re-read the error mechanism.\n\nActually, the `ensureFeatureFileAndStepDe
finitionScenarioHaveSameSteps` function is called by `defineFeature` (from `feat
ure-definition-creation.js`), not by `autoBindSteps` directly. The `defineFeatur
e` function compares `parsedScenarioSteps.length` with `scenarioFromStepDefiniti
ons.steps.length`.\n\nIn `automatic-step-binding.js`, `autoBindSteps` creates a 
custom `defineFeature` and calls it. Inside `test(scenario.title, function (opti
ons) { ... })`, it iterates over scenario steps and calls `options.defineStep(ma
tch.stepMatcher, match.stepFunction)` for each match.\n\nBut `options.defineStep
` is the function provided by `feature-definition-creation.js`'s `defineFeature`
implementation. It registers the step into `scenarioFromStepDefinitions.steps`.\
n\nSo if `matches.length === 1` for each step, then `scenarioFromStepDefinitions
.steps.length` should equal `parsedScenarioSteps.length`. If `matches.length ===
0`, an error is pushed to the `errors` array.\n\nBUT the error we're seeing is f
rom `ensureFeatureFileAndStepDefinitionScenarioHaveSameSteps`, which checks coun
ts BEFORE checking for missing matches. This means the validation in `feature-de
finition-creation.js` runs before the errors from `automatic-step-binding.js` ar
e thrown.\n\nWait, looking at `feature-definition-creation.js`:",
    encrypted=None
)
